summary.dataset_description: Dataset containing information about restaurants in the University District

properties.description: Type of cuisine served by the restaurant

goals.question: What is the most common cuisine served by the restaurants in the University District?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the dominant cuisine type in the area and can inform decisions on opening a new restaurant with a unique cuisine type.

goals.question: What is the distribution of restaurant locations in the University District?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude and longitude
goals.rationale: This helps to identify clusters of restaurants and can inform decisions on where to open a new restaurant.

goals.question: What is the average distance between restaurants in the University District?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the competition in the area and can inform decisions on pricing and marketing strategies.

goals.question: What is the relationship between cuisine type and restaurant rating in the University District?
goals.visualization: box plot of cuisine types and ratings
goals.rationale: This helps to identify which cuisine types tend to have higher ratings and can inform decisions on menu offerings.

goals.question: What is the correlation between restaurant rating and location in the University District?
goals.visualization: heat map of restaurant ratings and latitude/longitude
goals.rationale: This helps to identify areas with higher-rated restaurants and can inform decisions on where to open a new restaurant.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    cuisine_count = data['key'].value_counts()
    cuisine_count.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common cuisine served by the restaurants in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=cuisine_count.max(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend([f'Most common cuisine: {cuisine_count.idxmax()} ({cuisine_count.max():.2f})'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    ax.scatter(data['lat'], data['long'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of restaurant locations in the University District?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = data['lat'].astype(float)
    data['key'] = data['key'].astype(str)
    data = data.sort_values(by=['lat'])
    data['distance'] = data['lat'].diff()
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average distance between restaurants in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance between restaurants')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='rating', by='key', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Cuisine Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rating')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between cuisine type and restaurant rating in the University District?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    heatmap = ax.hexbin(data['lat'], data['rating'], gridsize=30, cmap='YlOrRd', bins='log')
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rating')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between restaurant rating and location in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar(heatmap, label='Number of Restaurants')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
